-------------------AJAX-------------------
Making requests (load,refresh, save data) without refreshing the page
AJAX - Asynchronous Javascript And XML
However, recently more and more people use JSON instead of XML and thus 
AJAJ - Asynchronous Javascript And JSON 
is the correct terminology. However, people generally mean AJAJ when the say AJAX

-------------------Web API-------------------
Making requests to particular http called end-points

APIs generally return stuff in JSON format

HTTP Status codes - https://api.cryptonator.com/api/ticker/btc-usd

<<<<<<<<< Fetch API >>>>>>>>>
- The newer Way of making requests via JS
- Supports promises!
- Not supported in Internet Explorer :(


-------------------JSON-------------------
JSON - Java Script Object Notation
can be used with other languages as well like python, etc
JSON validator - https://jsonformatter.curiousconcept.com/

 JSON.parse (text, [, reviver]) - used to parse a JSON file into JS object
 JSON.stringify (value[, replacer[, space]]) - used to parse a JS object into JSON
